WEBVTT

00:02.045 --> 00:04.047
[squeegee squeaking on window]

00:08.834 --> 00:10.880
[squeaking continues]

00:15.580 --> 00:16.668
MARISSA:
Diane?

00:16.712 --> 00:19.976
Want to use the conference room?

00:20.020 --> 00:22.674
Diane, would you want to use
the conference room instead?

00:22.718 --> 00:23.980
No, I'm fine.

00:25.503 --> 00:26.591
Did you hear what happened?

00:26.635 --> 00:28.724
What?

00:28.767 --> 00:31.031
It wasn't suicide. The guy
was trying to hang a banner

00:31.074 --> 00:32.075
on the roof.

00:32.119 --> 00:33.772
-Oh, my God.
-Yeah.

00:33.816 --> 00:35.644
"Fight the Hate."

00:35.687 --> 00:38.864
I guess he slipped and killed
two protesters on the street.

00:38.908 --> 00:41.128
That is... horrifying.

00:41.171 --> 00:42.868
It might get ugly today.

00:42.912 --> 00:45.219
The rumor is, he intentionally
jumped from our office

00:45.262 --> 00:48.091
-to kill two Proud Boys.
-Oh, geez, I give up.

00:48.135 --> 00:49.179
Diane, um,

00:49.223 --> 00:50.441
I'm ready.

00:50.485 --> 00:51.790
Oh.

00:51.834 --> 00:54.532
Good. How awful.

00:54.576 --> 00:56.186
Did you hear
it was somebody who slipped?

00:56.230 --> 00:58.580
And people think
he jumped from here.

00:58.623 --> 01:00.886
[sighs]:
God, that's crazy.

01:00.930 --> 01:03.106
All right, I'm-I'm headed out.
Do you want a ride?

01:03.150 --> 01:06.762
No, I'll catch up with you.
I have to gather my files.

01:10.157 --> 01:11.767
Whoa!

01:11.810 --> 01:13.856
[both laughing]

01:13.899 --> 01:15.162
God.

01:15.205 --> 01:17.947
CANDACE:
Was this found in the dorms?

01:17.990 --> 01:19.296
AVERY:
Yes, in the study room.

01:19.340 --> 01:22.038
CANDACE:
And this, where was this found?

01:22.082 --> 01:23.909
It was thrown through
one of the classroom windows.

01:23.953 --> 01:25.302
-That must have been terrifying.
-AVERY: It was.

01:25.346 --> 01:27.130
Everybody dove
under their desks.

01:27.174 --> 01:28.349
And what did
the school president do?

01:28.392 --> 01:30.351
AVERY:
She said, "Don't worry,

01:30.394 --> 01:32.657
the administration had
everything under control."

01:32.701 --> 01:34.398
CANDACE:
But there were five
other bomb threats

01:34.442 --> 01:36.139
-after that, weren't there?
-Yeah.

01:36.183 --> 01:37.793
That's when my parents said,
"You got to come home.

01:37.836 --> 01:39.142
-It's not safe anymore."
-And did you?

01:39.186 --> 01:41.840
Yes, but the school
wouldn't refund

01:41.884 --> 01:44.669
my tu-- our tuition.

01:44.713 --> 01:47.150
And that's why you're all here
in arbitration?

01:47.194 --> 01:49.718
-You and 58 other students?
-Yes.

01:49.761 --> 01:51.981
We want our tuition back.
We want to use the money

01:52.024 --> 01:54.636
-at a safer school...
-A whiter school.

01:54.679 --> 01:56.333
Let's not interrupt please,
Madam President.

01:56.377 --> 01:58.205
CANDACE:
No further questions.

01:58.248 --> 01:59.467
LOUIS:
Go ahead, ma'am.

01:59.510 --> 02:01.773
Uh... Mr. Jones,

02:01.817 --> 02:03.732
where did you go after you left
Wilson Clayman?

02:03.775 --> 02:04.950
What college?

02:04.994 --> 02:07.083
-Mm-hmm.
-AVERY: Notre Dame, but

02:07.127 --> 02:09.912
o-only because it-it was safer,

02:09.955 --> 02:11.696
-not because it was, uh...
-Whiter?

02:11.740 --> 02:13.916
I didn't say that.
No, I just meant "not as

02:13.959 --> 02:17.746
-alternative."
-Okay, so you were looking
for someplace safe

02:17.789 --> 02:20.009
from...

02:20.052 --> 02:21.706
this

02:21.750 --> 02:23.447
and this?

02:23.491 --> 02:25.188
AVERY:
They don't have to be real
to terrorize you.

02:25.232 --> 02:26.450
LOUIS:
What are you doing?

02:26.494 --> 02:28.539
Uh, this is
our firm's investigator.

02:28.583 --> 02:30.324
I just want him
to take a look at these.

02:30.367 --> 02:32.500
Mr. Jones, this is the
college enrollment contract...

02:32.543 --> 02:34.197
The same as the one
in our office?

02:34.241 --> 02:36.199
Well, they're terrorizing
Black institutions.

02:36.243 --> 02:37.766
Any idea who?

02:37.809 --> 02:39.507
Not yet.

02:39.550 --> 02:43.772
Now, in what way
is Wilson Clayman responsible

02:43.815 --> 02:45.339
for the current
protests happening

02:45.382 --> 02:46.818
-in Chicago?
-I can answer that.

02:46.862 --> 02:49.212
If you were witness,
I would welcome it.

02:49.256 --> 02:50.561
Mr. Cage, if Ms. Reddick
is finished,

02:50.605 --> 02:52.215
-I have an exhibit.
-Go ahead.

02:52.259 --> 02:54.478
I'm sickened to bear witness

02:54.522 --> 02:56.306
to the state of affairs
in this country.

02:56.350 --> 02:59.527
Books are being banned
and burned

02:59.570 --> 03:01.224
and hidden in the shadows

03:01.268 --> 03:03.183
to keep people ignorant,

03:03.226 --> 03:05.446
to keep people
out of their power.

03:05.489 --> 03:07.665
School districts
are fighting tooth

03:07.709 --> 03:11.234
and nail just so they don't
have to teach about race or

03:11.278 --> 03:13.280
racism or American history.

03:13.323 --> 03:15.020
It's disgusting

03:15.064 --> 03:16.587
and it's wrong.

03:16.631 --> 03:18.633
This is what I don't understand.

03:18.676 --> 03:22.071
If I said anything like that
about anti-white bias,

03:22.114 --> 03:23.812
I would be called racist.

03:23.855 --> 03:25.944
COMMENTATOR [over TV]:
She's an educator. She shouldn't

03:25.988 --> 03:28.599
be trying to start a race war.

03:28.643 --> 03:30.993
The first bomb threat came
two days after Ms. Allen-Hellman

03:31.036 --> 03:32.951
made these remarks.
If she hadn't given

03:32.995 --> 03:34.866
her little speech,
Wilson Clayman

03:34.910 --> 03:36.651
wouldn't have become a target.

03:36.694 --> 03:38.218
That's why the college
is responsible.

03:38.261 --> 03:40.742
So, you're saying
we brought this on ourselves?

03:40.785 --> 03:42.265
-Madam President...
-ANGELA: No, I will not

03:42.309 --> 03:43.832
hold my tongue

03:43.875 --> 03:47.270
and allow white supremacy
to control the narrative.

03:49.141 --> 03:51.405
These kids and their parents,

03:51.448 --> 03:54.364
they want to bankrupt my school.

03:54.408 --> 03:57.106
We can't afford
to refund tuition.

03:57.149 --> 04:00.805
That's why it might be time to
pursue your liability insurance.

04:00.849 --> 04:02.285
That means
we're admitting fault?

04:02.329 --> 04:03.939
No, it means that
you're being smart.

04:05.810 --> 04:07.116
We're not paying.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.728
That's-that's not an option,
Mr. Sandel.

04:10.772 --> 04:13.122
-You are the school's insurer.
-EDWARD: Yeah, Ridley Mutual

04:13.165 --> 04:14.863
is not recognizing your claim.

04:14.906 --> 04:16.691
DIANE:
The injury to students' academic

04:16.734 --> 04:20.564
experience was due to threats
made from unknown parties.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.087
In other words, terrorism.

04:22.131 --> 04:24.176
The school's policy
insures against that.

04:24.220 --> 04:26.004
Well, uh, "terrorism," uh,

04:26.048 --> 04:28.268
is defined as "violence or

04:28.311 --> 04:30.095
"the threat of violence absent

04:30.139 --> 04:32.402
provocation,"
so your arbitration already,

04:32.446 --> 04:35.144
uh, proved that the
terrorist acts were based on

04:35.187 --> 04:36.319
President Hellman's speech.

04:36.363 --> 04:39.453
Oh, my God, this is Kafkaesque.

04:39.496 --> 04:41.150
[crowd shouting outside]

04:42.630 --> 04:44.675
LIZ:
Uh, Mr. Sandel, uh, we

04:44.719 --> 04:47.330
contest your interpretation
of the policy's language,

04:47.374 --> 04:48.810
and we are prepared
to take legal action.

04:48.853 --> 04:50.855
See you in court.

04:52.988 --> 04:54.511
Well, this can't be good.

04:54.555 --> 04:56.426
DIANE:
Good luck.

04:56.470 --> 04:57.775
Thank you.

05:02.650 --> 05:04.565
Oh.

05:04.608 --> 05:06.654
There she is, Princess Di.

05:06.697 --> 05:08.177
-[laughs]
-Oh.

05:08.220 --> 05:09.570
-WINSTON: How's Kurt doing?
-Well, thank you.

05:09.613 --> 05:11.528
Tell him I want his dekes.

05:11.572 --> 05:12.660
-[laughs]
-Oh.

05:12.703 --> 05:15.184
[chuckles] Dekes are decoys.

05:15.227 --> 05:16.446
They-they went
duck hunting together.

05:16.490 --> 05:18.230
Oh.

05:18.274 --> 05:21.016
So, what do we need down here?
Oh, no, no,

05:21.059 --> 05:22.844
you stay, too.

05:24.846 --> 05:27.675
Well, um, we didn't expect
to see you gentlemen down here,

05:27.718 --> 05:29.154
but thank you
for taking our meeting.

05:29.198 --> 05:31.200
Uh, not to take up
too much of your time,

05:31.243 --> 05:33.333
we'd like to review a few

05:33.376 --> 05:36.248
financial issues.

05:36.292 --> 05:38.816
Yes, uh, well, despite

05:38.860 --> 05:40.688
international disruptions,

05:40.731 --> 05:42.951
uh, this past quarter
has been stronger than expected.

05:42.994 --> 05:44.387
That was noted. Well done.

05:44.431 --> 05:46.476
And being under your umbrella

05:46.520 --> 05:48.435
has been very beneficial,

05:48.478 --> 05:50.828
and we do not
take that for granted.

05:50.872 --> 05:52.526
However, uh,

05:52.569 --> 05:54.876
we have noticed
that our equity partners

05:54.919 --> 05:56.225
are two weeks behind

05:56.268 --> 05:58.358
in their pay.

05:58.401 --> 06:00.316
Have you checked
with accounting?

06:00.360 --> 06:01.317
RI'CHARD:
We have.

06:01.361 --> 06:03.275
It's not coming from them.

06:03.319 --> 06:06.409
As you might imagine, uh,
there's been a bit of grumbling.

06:06.453 --> 06:08.019
How odd.

06:09.673 --> 06:11.545
WINSTON:
To be honest with you,

06:11.588 --> 06:13.982
the Russian sanctions
over Ukraine

06:14.025 --> 06:15.418
have affected our business

06:15.462 --> 06:17.942
-more than we anticipated.
-LIZ: How so?

06:17.986 --> 06:19.857
We're not receiving payments
from some of our clients.

06:19.901 --> 06:21.990
Russian clients?

06:22.033 --> 06:24.819
It's from past work,
money owed, not new clients,

06:24.862 --> 06:26.516
but the U.S. government

06:26.560 --> 06:28.344
is still confiscating our money.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.345
RI'CHARD:
And, um,

06:29.389 --> 06:30.781
what can we do?

06:30.825 --> 06:32.217
WINSTON:
We have a date in court

06:32.261 --> 06:35.351
to argue for our funds
to be released.

06:35.395 --> 06:38.441
What would be helpful is
if you argued for us.

06:38.485 --> 06:41.618
OSMAN:
They're biased against us
for our accents

06:41.662 --> 06:43.925
and our international business.

06:43.968 --> 06:47.319
It would be good
to have local color.

06:48.582 --> 06:51.062
[stammers] We don't mean
"color" in that way.

06:51.106 --> 06:53.021
[chuckles]

06:53.064 --> 06:55.763
Oh, good thing the government
loves Black lawyers so much.

06:57.460 --> 07:00.245
I'll-I'll tell Kurt
you said hello.

07:01.725 --> 07:03.640
Diane.

07:03.684 --> 07:05.425
Are you okay?

07:05.468 --> 07:06.991
What do you mean?

07:07.035 --> 07:09.603
Well, I-I think you should take
a day or two off.

07:09.646 --> 07:12.344
You just saw a man die
right in front of you.

07:12.388 --> 07:14.869
Oh, no, no, I'm... I'm fine.

07:14.912 --> 07:17.785
I just, I need a few hours.
I'll just go walk

07:17.828 --> 07:20.309
-in the sunshine.
-Okay. Good.

07:20.352 --> 07:22.050
Good, go. Work can manage

07:22.093 --> 07:24.705
without you for a few hours,
and I'll see you in court.

07:24.748 --> 07:26.184
Okay.

07:28.273 --> 07:30.928
-[classical music playing]
-[water bubbling]

07:30.972 --> 07:32.800
[sighs]

07:32.843 --> 07:35.629
"My heart leaps up..."

07:37.457 --> 07:40.677
"...when I behold
a rainbow in the sky."

07:43.463 --> 07:46.378
"So was it when my life began."

07:47.945 --> 07:51.862
"So is it now I am...

07:51.906 --> 07:53.821
woman."

08:01.481 --> 08:03.483
[monitor beeping]

08:18.933 --> 08:20.195
How are you doing?

08:20.238 --> 08:22.937
People keep asking
if I'm all right.

08:22.980 --> 08:24.982
Are you?

08:25.026 --> 08:27.724
Well... [sighs] I saw a man

08:27.768 --> 08:30.118
d-die outside my window.

08:30.161 --> 08:33.077
-What?
-He fell from the roof
of our building

08:33.121 --> 08:36.646
-onto my balustrade.
-Oh, my God. That's awful.

08:36.690 --> 08:39.519
The world is pretty awful now,

08:39.562 --> 08:42.913
but-but then I come here,
and I...

08:42.957 --> 08:44.219
I feel good.

08:45.655 --> 08:48.092
So, is... [chuckles]
is that the secret?

08:48.136 --> 08:49.485
I just need to keep coming here?

08:49.529 --> 08:52.140
No. I mean, you can, but,

08:52.183 --> 08:54.795
eventually, the pleasure
will dissipate,

08:54.838 --> 08:56.623
and you'll suffer withdrawals.

08:56.666 --> 08:59.016
Oh, God. What then?

09:00.452 --> 09:02.063
Have you ever heard
of the "four sights"?

09:02.106 --> 09:04.282
Is that the new show
at the Art...

09:04.326 --> 09:05.980
Art Institute? Oh, no, no, no,

09:06.023 --> 09:08.025
-that's Buddha, right?
-Yes.

09:08.069 --> 09:09.679
Prince Siddhartha.

09:09.723 --> 09:11.551
He ventured outside his palace
for the first time,

09:11.594 --> 09:15.424
and he saw four sights
that changed him forever.

09:15.467 --> 09:19.080
Aging, disease, and death.

09:19.123 --> 09:20.472
-He saw a rotting corpse.
-Are you a Buddhist?

09:20.516 --> 09:22.300
-I am.
-Really?

09:22.344 --> 09:24.607
-Really.
-Wow. You don't seem like one.

09:24.651 --> 09:27.175
-I hide it very well.
-[laughs]

09:28.785 --> 09:30.918
So, what is the-the
fourth sight?

09:30.961 --> 09:34.051
You mentioned three.
What's... beyond death?

09:34.095 --> 09:36.184
He met an ascetic.

09:36.227 --> 09:38.534
Someone who renounced
all his possessions,

09:38.578 --> 09:40.623
and he realized that was
the only way to escape

09:40.667 --> 09:43.234
the changeability of life.

09:43.278 --> 09:45.019
You trying to convert me?

09:45.062 --> 09:47.978
No, but if you want to take
a Buddhist personality test,

09:48.022 --> 09:49.066
I can make a call.

09:50.198 --> 09:51.155
That was a joke.

09:51.199 --> 09:54.245
Oh. God. Sorry.

09:54.289 --> 09:56.639
Yeah, religion... scares me.

09:56.683 --> 09:59.773
It was the same with me.

10:01.731 --> 10:04.429
Yes, I've been looking at that.
What is it?

10:04.473 --> 10:06.170
It's a dorje.

10:06.214 --> 10:08.782
It's a diamond
and a thunderbolt.

10:08.825 --> 10:11.001
To help you find steadiness
in your life.

10:11.045 --> 10:12.481
Well, I can't take this.

10:12.524 --> 10:14.309
Just bring it back
to your next session.

10:14.352 --> 10:16.746
We can talk about it.

10:43.251 --> 10:45.296
♪

10:52.347 --> 10:54.175
[knock on door]

10:59.397 --> 11:02.531
-Everything all right?
-Yes, I-I forgot something.

11:02.574 --> 11:04.446
-Your phone?
-No.

11:07.536 --> 11:09.669
[moans] Just that.

11:13.673 --> 11:15.283
[sighs]

11:15.326 --> 11:19.200
Oh... [laughs]

11:21.811 --> 11:24.466
-You wench.
-[elevator bell dings]

11:29.166 --> 11:32.866
[laughs]

11:34.563 --> 11:37.087
[buzzer sounds]

11:37.131 --> 11:39.655
Anything in your pockets, ma'am?

11:39.699 --> 11:41.831
Oh... oh, yeah.

11:41.875 --> 11:43.790
Sorry. This.

11:48.142 --> 11:50.013
What is this?

11:50.057 --> 11:53.495
Oh, nothing. It's just,
um, a religious object.

11:53.538 --> 11:55.584
A dorje?

11:55.627 --> 11:57.629
Yes. Thank you, Your Honor.

11:57.673 --> 12:00.154
I, uh, I have one myself.

12:00.197 --> 12:03.505
Om Tara tu Tara tu ray swaha.

12:03.548 --> 12:06.247
Yeah, diamond and thunderbolt.

12:08.205 --> 12:10.730
LIZ:
As our firm's investigator,
you've been

12:10.773 --> 12:12.732
monitoring the protests
throughout the city,

12:12.775 --> 12:14.603
-correct?
-I've talked to a lot of people
on the streets

12:14.646 --> 12:16.387
to get a handle
on what's going on.

12:16.431 --> 12:20.174
And in those conversations,
has a common theme emerged?

12:20.217 --> 12:22.263
-Fox News.
-Your Honor, objection.

12:22.306 --> 12:25.396
If Wilson Clayman wants to sue
Fox News, then let them do it.

12:25.440 --> 12:29.052
I agree, Counselor,
how is this germane?

12:29.096 --> 12:30.271
Ms. Lockhart?

12:30.314 --> 12:32.012
Oh.

12:32.055 --> 12:35.493
Your Honor, we're merely
showing that Ridley Mutual

12:35.537 --> 12:37.844
is in breach of contract because

12:37.887 --> 12:39.062
they're blaming the victim.

12:39.106 --> 12:40.760
Ah-- This is crazy.

12:40.803 --> 12:42.674
-Excuse me, could I finish?
-MEACHEM: Yes, please.

12:42.718 --> 12:46.504
Mr. Sandel,
let's keep this calm.

12:46.548 --> 12:48.811
Thank you, Your Honor.
Ridley Mutual

12:48.855 --> 12:52.162
wants to blame the president
of Wilson Clayman because

12:52.206 --> 12:55.949
she made a speech,
but that speech was a response

12:55.992 --> 12:58.038
to a Ted Willoughby rant

12:58.081 --> 12:59.953
about racism in Chicago,

12:59.996 --> 13:03.521
and that would seem to be
the first cause.

13:04.740 --> 13:06.786
MEACHEM:
Okay, here's what I suggest.

13:06.829 --> 13:09.527
As much as I appreciate opinion,

13:09.571 --> 13:12.922
I would rather have counselors
return with evidence.

13:12.966 --> 13:15.055
[gavel bangs]

13:15.098 --> 13:17.797
You have any idea who might be
terrorizing the school?

13:17.840 --> 13:19.146
I might.

13:19.189 --> 13:21.017
Well, it would really
help us in court.

13:21.061 --> 13:23.193
-Mm.
-Let me see what I can do.

13:24.978 --> 13:27.589
Well, that walk in the sun
really seemed to help you.

13:27.632 --> 13:29.721
Yeah, it did.

13:29.765 --> 13:32.637
Liz, have you ever
explored Buddhism?

13:32.681 --> 13:34.944
No. Is that
what's doing it to you?

13:34.988 --> 13:36.816
-I don't know.
-Mm.

13:36.859 --> 13:39.862
Can something act on you
without your knowing it?

13:39.906 --> 13:42.909
I don't know.
Is something acting on you?

13:42.952 --> 13:44.606
-Maybe.
-[both chuckle]
-[elevator bell dings]

13:44.649 --> 13:47.043
I feel light-hearted.

13:47.087 --> 13:49.306
Well, I'm happy for you.

13:49.350 --> 13:52.135
PROTESTERS [chanting]:
You will not replace us!

13:52.179 --> 13:55.051
You will not
replace us!

13:55.095 --> 13:56.487
You will not

13:56.531 --> 13:58.011
replace us!

13:58.054 --> 14:00.665
You will not replace us!

14:00.709 --> 14:03.625
You will not
replace us!

14:03.668 --> 14:07.194
You will not replace us!

14:07.237 --> 14:09.283
[protesters continue
chanting faintly]

14:10.458 --> 14:11.763
Are you carrying?

14:34.134 --> 14:35.831
So, you know who's throwing
these decoy grenades?

14:40.401 --> 14:42.142
Where are we going?

14:42.185 --> 14:44.231
Renetta wants to see you.

14:48.496 --> 14:51.716
No, we don't have time.
They'll burn themselves out.

14:51.760 --> 14:53.762
Just get video.

14:56.156 --> 14:57.548
Is this about the protests?

14:57.592 --> 15:00.943
The protests aren't the problem.

15:00.987 --> 15:02.336
It's what comes after.

15:02.379 --> 15:04.207
And what's that?

15:22.399 --> 15:24.184
