32:11.799 --> 32:14.367
-Good news and bad news.
-Uh, really bad news.

32:14.410 --> 32:16.195
The good news is

32:16.238 --> 32:18.110
that our paralegal
Susan Tremont

32:18.153 --> 32:19.459
probably isn't
a white supremacist.

32:19.502 --> 32:21.417
Okay. What's the
really bad news?

32:21.461 --> 32:23.942
[sighs] She's an FBI agent.

32:31.253 --> 32:32.907
I tracked her to an address
at an office park in Winnetka.

32:32.951 --> 32:34.213
Regional office of the FBI.

32:34.256 --> 32:35.736
What about that photo?

32:35.779 --> 32:37.346
Her meeting
with the white supremacists.

32:37.390 --> 32:40.784
We think that might be part
of her work for the FBI.

32:40.828 --> 32:43.004
What does the FBI want with us?

32:43.048 --> 32:45.659
Maybe they're going
after STR Laurie.

32:45.702 --> 32:48.096
But maybe they're also
going after us.

32:51.056 --> 32:54.494
What do you know
about Susan Tremont?

32:55.799 --> 32:58.933
Paralegal. Friendly. Eager.

32:58.977 --> 33:00.761
LIZ:
How so?

33:00.804 --> 33:04.373
She asks questions, and I try,
as a second-year,

33:04.417 --> 33:05.940
to help her when I have time.

33:05.984 --> 33:08.464
Have you included her
in any of your cases?

33:08.508 --> 33:10.553
Just the discrimination suit.

33:12.991 --> 33:15.210
May I ask, why the questions?

33:15.254 --> 33:16.733
Your files are
password-protected, I assume.

33:16.777 --> 33:18.300
Of course.

33:18.344 --> 33:20.520
You have high-profile clients.
Oscar Rivi,

33:20.563 --> 33:22.957
Wolfe-Colman, Ben-Baruch,

33:23.001 --> 33:24.785
-among others.
-CARMEN: Yes.

33:24.828 --> 33:26.352
Has Susan asked about them?

33:30.051 --> 33:32.619
Not specifically. Just a...

33:32.662 --> 33:35.187
-general interest.
-LIZ: We, of course, assume

33:35.230 --> 33:36.884
that you've never crossed

33:36.927 --> 33:39.756
any legal line to help them.

33:39.800 --> 33:41.062
Have you?

33:41.106 --> 33:42.585
Is Susan a cop?

33:42.629 --> 33:45.023
Is she an undercover cop?

33:45.066 --> 33:47.199
No.

33:47.242 --> 33:48.722
She's FBI.

33:49.940 --> 33:50.941
Oh, fuck.

33:50.985 --> 33:53.161
You are confident

33:53.205 --> 33:55.294
that you have not
shown her anything,

33:55.337 --> 33:57.557
or done anything illegal?

33:59.472 --> 34:00.864
Carmen?

34:00.908 --> 34:02.344
[hits desk]

34:03.824 --> 34:05.086
She's after Ben-Baruch.

34:05.130 --> 34:07.349
She's been asking about

34:07.393 --> 34:09.656
getting deeper into his case.

34:09.699 --> 34:11.527
Okay.

34:11.571 --> 34:14.356
You need to assign her
to busy work.

34:14.400 --> 34:15.923
Don't brush her off.

34:15.966 --> 34:17.794
Keep her on some earlier filing.

34:17.838 --> 34:19.927
Ben-Baruch's immigration case.

34:19.970 --> 34:21.537
Oh, good. That's completed work.

34:21.581 --> 34:24.105
LIZ: Yeah, and make her think
it's a step up,

34:24.149 --> 34:26.586
-like a promotion,
that you love her work.
-Mm.

34:28.631 --> 34:30.198
We shouldn't be talking
about this down here.

34:30.242 --> 34:31.199
She'll get suspicious.

34:31.243 --> 34:32.722
True.

34:32.766 --> 34:34.159
Wait.

34:34.202 --> 34:36.900
Have her do the filing
on the union case,

34:36.944 --> 34:38.772
the teamsters case
from last year.

34:38.815 --> 34:39.860
Why?

34:39.903 --> 34:42.993
It'll come in handy. Trust me.

34:46.693 --> 34:48.782
[door opens, closes]

34:53.395 --> 34:54.701
What do we think?

34:54.744 --> 34:56.616
LIZ:
Carmen hates being tricked.

34:56.659 --> 34:57.921
She'll do wonders for us.

34:57.965 --> 34:59.662
I agree.

34:59.706 --> 35:01.360
We have to get to court.

35:01.403 --> 35:03.492
Yup. You, too.

35:04.493 --> 35:07.453
Thank you, Mr. Willoughby,
for joining us.

35:07.496 --> 35:10.369
My duty as an American,
lawyer man.

35:10.412 --> 35:12.414
-Your Honor.
-Mr. Willoughby.

35:12.458 --> 35:14.721
This isn't your first time

35:14.764 --> 35:17.419
in a courtroom, is it,
Mr. Carlson-- I mean,

35:17.463 --> 35:19.943
Mr. Tucker-- I'm sorry,
Mr., uh, Willoughby?

35:19.987 --> 35:21.467
No. It's sort of surprising

35:21.510 --> 35:23.860
because I'm actually
a very nice guy.

35:23.904 --> 35:26.515
But you and your employer
were sued

35:26.559 --> 35:28.778
in... 2020,

35:28.822 --> 35:31.041
-weren't you?
-Go figure.

35:31.085 --> 35:34.697
-Is that a yes?
-Uh, sorry. Yes. [laughs]

35:34.741 --> 35:38.048
EDWARD:
[chuckles] A-And what did that
lawsuit accuse you of?

35:38.092 --> 35:41.182
Uh, defamation, slander,
stuff like that.

35:41.226 --> 35:43.706
Wh-- You won that case,
didn't you?

35:43.750 --> 35:46.709
I did. We did, which was nice.

35:46.753 --> 35:48.015
Objection. Relevance.

35:48.058 --> 35:50.322
Well, I have some time.

35:50.365 --> 35:52.846
Let's see what the relevance is.

35:52.889 --> 35:54.848
EDWARD:
Do you remember why the judge

35:54.891 --> 35:57.372
sided with you in that case,
Mr. Willoughby?

35:57.416 --> 36:00.332
TED:
Basically, he said that
no reasonable person

36:00.375 --> 36:01.768
should take me seriously,

36:01.811 --> 36:03.596
which sounds like an insult,

36:03.639 --> 36:06.120
but Tucker Carlson got
the same pass, and he gets

36:06.164 --> 36:09.254
paid millions a year,
so that's pretty serious.

36:09.297 --> 36:12.474
Okay, and why should
no reasonable person

36:12.518 --> 36:13.954
take you seriously?

36:13.997 --> 36:17.087
Well, what I do
is more like commentary.

36:17.131 --> 36:19.786
Like Tucker.
You know, non-literal,

36:19.829 --> 36:21.962
non-factual. It's just for fun.

36:22.005 --> 36:25.748
[chuckles] So, uh,
blaming you for violence

36:25.792 --> 36:29.404
or the-the threat of violence
would be absurd?

36:29.448 --> 36:31.580
I am against violence.
Everybody knows that.

36:31.624 --> 36:33.539
Look behind them.

36:33.582 --> 36:34.975
EDWARD:
Uh, no further questions.

36:36.455 --> 36:38.065
Willoughby's lawyer?

36:38.108 --> 36:39.806
-My guess.
-Okay.

36:39.849 --> 36:42.112
Mr. Willoughby...

36:42.156 --> 36:43.462
Ted's fine.

36:43.505 --> 36:46.116
Uh, Ted, um,

36:46.160 --> 36:49.076
your shows, which you described
as "just for fun,"

36:49.119 --> 36:51.687
they take on some
pretty serious issues,

36:51.731 --> 36:53.689
-don't they?
-That depends.

36:53.733 --> 36:55.604
Abortion. Immigration.

36:55.648 --> 36:58.085
Ukraine. Putin. Trump.

36:58.128 --> 37:01.219
I'd-I'd call those
serious issues, wouldn't you?

37:01.262 --> 37:03.830
Sure. I like dealing
with issues.

37:03.873 --> 37:06.398
Well, in the, in the last year,

37:06.441 --> 37:09.270
you have done 74 segments

37:09.314 --> 37:11.098
on "Black on white violence"

37:11.141 --> 37:13.927
-in Chicago.
-TED: [scoffs] Somebody counted?

37:13.970 --> 37:16.016
LIZ:
Not to mention

37:16.059 --> 37:19.280
all the stories you did
mentioning college president,

37:19.324 --> 37:21.021
Angela Allen-Hellman,

37:21.064 --> 37:22.979
-by name.
-I'm so flattered.

37:23.023 --> 37:25.765
Mr. Willoughby,
why are you biased

37:25.808 --> 37:26.809
-against Black people?
-Objection.

37:26.853 --> 37:28.071
MEACHEM:
Sustained.

37:28.115 --> 37:29.725
Oh, my God, I'm not biased.

37:29.769 --> 37:32.293
Somebody attacked me
at my Connecticut feed store

37:32.337 --> 37:35.122
and said the same thing,
and I said, "I'm not a bad guy."

37:35.165 --> 37:37.690
Each morning,
we get a network memo,

37:37.733 --> 37:40.388
and they decide what we cover.

37:42.042 --> 37:44.740
-[whispering]
-[Diane mouths]

37:44.784 --> 37:46.742
TED:
I'm just the messenger.

37:46.786 --> 37:50.180
Mr. Willoughby, this
"network memo," who writes it?

37:51.965 --> 37:53.793
Gosh. I don't know exactly who.

37:53.836 --> 37:56.404
It just tells us how to keep

37:56.448 --> 37:57.927
the audience enraged-- engaged!

37:57.971 --> 37:59.755
EDWARD: Uh...
[clears throat] Your Honor,

37:59.799 --> 38:01.801
uh, I ask for a short recess.

38:01.844 --> 38:03.411
I'll bet you do.

38:05.065 --> 38:06.371
[clears throat]

38:06.414 --> 38:07.981
EDWARD:
All right, we'll settle.

38:08.024 --> 38:09.635
ANGELA:
Ah. Expect to pay

38:09.678 --> 38:11.724
through the nose after
putting us through all this.

38:11.767 --> 38:13.508
That's fine.
The funds aren't coming

38:13.552 --> 38:15.075
-from Ridley Mutual.
-It's Fox, isn't it?

38:15.118 --> 38:17.730
Uh, cost-benefit analysis.

38:17.773 --> 38:20.950
Paying you versus allowing one
of their network stars to say

38:20.994 --> 38:22.125
one more fucking word
off-script.

38:22.169 --> 38:24.519
Okay, we'll talk
numbers tomorrow.

38:24.563 --> 38:27.043
-You wanted to see me?
-Uh, you've been asking

38:27.087 --> 38:29.263
if I have any
extra work for you.

38:29.307 --> 38:30.786
Does that offer still stand?

38:30.830 --> 38:33.485
Absolutely. It would be
my pleasure to help.

38:33.528 --> 38:35.878
Great. These files
are essential,

38:35.922 --> 38:39.142
but someone threw off the
alphabetization and the dates.

38:39.186 --> 38:40.318
Look through them closely

38:40.361 --> 38:42.058
and organize them for me?

38:42.102 --> 38:44.365
Yeah, on it.
What-What's the case about?

38:44.409 --> 38:47.063
-Oh, you'll see.
-Okay.

38:52.591 --> 38:54.767
LIZ:
Look at that.

38:54.810 --> 38:57.204
Looks almost like
nothing ever happened.

38:58.205 --> 39:00.425
[chuckles] I kind of
like him headless.

39:00.468 --> 39:03.123
Mm. Looks good from the street.

39:05.604 --> 39:08.215
So, how is your
Buddhism thing going?

39:08.258 --> 39:10.086
Om...

39:10.130 --> 39:12.306
-I don't know.
-[both laughing]

39:14.003 --> 39:16.397
Liz?

39:16.441 --> 39:18.791
-Yes?
-Can we share secrets?

39:18.834 --> 39:20.836
Oh, I hope so.

39:20.880 --> 39:22.882
Mm, no, as in,

39:22.925 --> 39:25.014
you can never tell anyone.

39:25.058 --> 39:27.234
Oh, fuck, tell me.

39:30.890 --> 39:32.631
I kissed my doctor.

39:32.674 --> 39:35.285
Your doctor?

39:35.329 --> 39:36.983
I can still feel it.

39:37.026 --> 39:39.551
I mean, it was... it was a kiss.

39:39.594 --> 39:41.988
And did he kiss you back?

39:43.337 --> 39:45.426
Well, he didn't pull away,

39:45.470 --> 39:48.081
but he didn't pull me
to him, so...

39:48.124 --> 39:49.474
I'm not sure.

39:49.517 --> 39:51.954
I don't think
I could kiss my doctor.

39:51.998 --> 39:54.479
[both laugh]

39:54.522 --> 39:58.396
Wait, did you-- were you wearing
a paper gown? [laughs]

39:58.439 --> 40:00.310
Diane?

40:00.354 --> 40:03.096
He was standing in the doorway,

40:03.139 --> 40:05.881
and he gave me this.

40:05.925 --> 40:07.492
Oh, no.

40:07.535 --> 40:09.363
-What happened?
-LIZ: What is that?

40:09.407 --> 40:10.408
What kind of doctor is this?

40:12.018 --> 40:15.282
You know him. Lyle Bettencourt.

40:15.325 --> 40:18.503
Wait, is he the one that
testified in the gene therapy--

40:18.546 --> 40:21.462
Wait, the... silver hair
and the glasses?

40:21.506 --> 40:23.682
Okay, yes. Yes, I approve.

40:23.725 --> 40:25.988
Yes, you can kiss him.
Wait, can I kiss him?

40:26.032 --> 40:27.207
No! Only me.

40:27.250 --> 40:28.774
-[both laughing]
-He is gorgeous.

40:28.817 --> 40:31.777
I know.

40:31.820 --> 40:34.780
And he can talk
about Verdi and Dante

40:34.823 --> 40:36.738
and Dahlia Lithwick.

40:36.782 --> 40:40.002
[laughing] Wow.

40:40.046 --> 40:44.485
Okay. All right, so,
now I am going to ask you

40:44.529 --> 40:47.662
the here-it-is question...

40:47.706 --> 40:50.448
Where's Kurt?

40:50.491 --> 40:51.927
I mean, he's away again,

40:51.971 --> 40:54.930
working for the NRA.

40:54.974 --> 40:57.759
He's... he's away a lot.

40:57.803 --> 41:01.154
Well, and even when he,
when he's here, I mean...

41:02.808 --> 41:04.853
[sighs] It was one thing

41:04.897 --> 41:07.247
to be political opposites
years ago,

41:07.290 --> 41:09.771
but now, I mean...

41:09.815 --> 41:11.730
I mean, the divide is...

41:11.773 --> 41:13.427
a chasm.

41:13.471 --> 41:15.560
Gun control. Roe v. Wade.

41:15.603 --> 41:17.736
The Supreme Court.

41:17.779 --> 41:19.912
Diane, I was

41:19.955 --> 41:22.175
married and divorced twice,

41:22.218 --> 41:24.438
and I would suggest

41:24.482 --> 41:28.224
that you figure out
what you really want,

41:28.268 --> 41:31.140
and not just what you think
you want at the moment.

41:32.794 --> 41:34.448
You have regrets?

41:34.492 --> 41:37.059
[groans] Wow.

41:37.103 --> 41:38.800
There's always regrets.

41:38.844 --> 41:41.237
With Adrian, or...

41:41.281 --> 41:44.023
What-what was
the other one's name?

41:44.066 --> 41:46.895
Ian. [laughs]

41:46.939 --> 41:50.638
A-- Well, Adrian...
Adrian was impossible.

41:50.682 --> 41:52.422
And with Ian, I...

41:54.381 --> 41:57.863
I don't know, maybe I was
the one who was impossible.

42:00.169 --> 42:02.041
But divorce is hell.

42:04.565 --> 42:06.219
Yeah, but you seem happy.

42:07.742 --> 42:10.658
That's 'cause I love my son.

42:10.702 --> 42:12.486
Oh, he is so much fun.

42:13.487 --> 42:14.880
Hmm.

42:14.923 --> 42:16.621
Well, I don't have that.

42:16.664 --> 42:19.667
What are you gonna do?

42:19.711 --> 42:22.409
[sighs] I honestly don't know.

42:22.452 --> 42:23.889
[laughs]

42:23.932 --> 42:27.370
-Diane.
-However,

42:27.414 --> 42:30.243
I do have
an appointment tomorrow.

42:30.286 --> 42:32.593
[laughs]
Well, then,

42:32.637 --> 42:34.987
I think you should
take it much further.

42:35.030 --> 42:37.032
-I know. Really. Right?
-Yes.

42:37.076 --> 42:39.165
-All the way. Right?
-Wait. Yes.

42:39.208 --> 42:40.340
Why not?

42:40.383 --> 42:41.602
♪ Oh, Jesus, I love you♪

42:41.646 --> 42:43.865
♪ And I love Buddha, too♪

42:43.909 --> 42:45.127
-♪ Ramakrishna, Guru Dev♪
-Yes. Yes!

42:45.171 --> 42:46.476
Yes! [laughs]

42:46.520 --> 42:47.782
♪ Tao Te Ching and Mohammed♪

42:47.826 --> 42:49.697
♪ Why do some people say♪

42:49.741 --> 42:51.003
-♪ That there
is just one way...♪
-Get it!

42:51.046 --> 42:53.614
-Come with me, girl.
-Yeah. Yes.

42:53.658 --> 42:55.616
We need a doctor.

42:55.660 --> 42:56.878
Call the doctor.
Call the doctor.

42:56.922 --> 42:59.664
-Does he have a brother?
-[laughter]

42:59.707 --> 43:03.450
♪ I love you
and Buddha, too, all right♪

43:03.493 --> 43:07.323
-♪ All right, all right♪
-♪ I love you, Jesus♪

43:07.367 --> 43:10.936
♪ I love you and Buddha, too,
all right, all right.♪

43:16.637 --> 43:18.378
It's come to our attention
that the FBI is planning

43:18.421 --> 43:20.380
to pursue a case
against STR Laurie.

43:21.381 --> 43:23.513
That's not something
I can discuss with you.

43:23.557 --> 43:25.254
We're not here to discuss it.

43:25.298 --> 43:27.430
We're here to share this
with you.

43:27.474 --> 43:30.477
You can go after STS Laurie
if you so desire,

43:30.520 --> 43:33.654
but we are prepared to expose
your unconstitutional

43:33.698 --> 43:36.309
search and seizure in the
warehouse union investigation.

43:36.352 --> 43:38.703
[scoffs]

43:38.746 --> 43:41.706
The FBI isn't involved
in any union investigation.

43:41.749 --> 43:44.534
And even if we were, that has
nothing to do with this.

43:44.578 --> 43:47.494
Ah. But we have evidence.

43:47.537 --> 43:49.409
I love a bluff.

43:51.541 --> 43:53.413
Carmen?

43:53.456 --> 43:55.284
Hi. I'm Carmen Moyo.

43:55.328 --> 43:57.591
I've been working with your
undercover agent Susan Tremont.

43:59.201 --> 44:00.681
No idea who you're
talking about.

44:00.725 --> 44:02.074
Let me refresh your memory.

44:02.117 --> 44:05.512
This is Susan Tremont.

44:05.555 --> 44:08.384
Your undercover agent.

44:08.428 --> 44:09.734
Will not confirm or deny
if I know this...

44:09.777 --> 44:11.387
This is Susan Tremont.

44:11.431 --> 44:14.086
This is also Susan Tremont.

44:14.129 --> 44:16.610
And my personal favorite,
a close-up of,

44:16.654 --> 44:20.527
you guessed it, Susan Tremont
working on our teamster case,

44:20.570 --> 44:24.792
organizing files and
scanning every single one.

44:24.836 --> 44:26.098
We also have video.

44:30.624 --> 44:32.408
I have no idea
who gave her permission

44:32.452 --> 44:35.194
to search these files, or how
you think this is relevant,

44:35.237 --> 44:37.109
but... [exhales sharply]

44:37.152 --> 44:40.329
that's all the time
I have for you today.

44:40.373 --> 44:41.722
-Excuse me.
-It's gonna be hard

44:41.766 --> 44:43.419
to prosecute your
upcoming teamster case

44:43.463 --> 44:45.204
if one of your agents has
reviewed our files.

44:47.423 --> 44:50.165
I'm needed in my next meeting.

44:50.209 --> 44:52.951
I would leave us alone,
Agent Morris.

45:01.655 --> 45:03.962
Okay, did that work?

45:04.005 --> 45:07.443
-I don't know.
-I saw a flicker

45:07.487 --> 45:09.532
of recognition.

45:09.576 --> 45:12.013
Will that flicker
stand up in court?

45:14.973 --> 45:18.106
♪

45:18.150 --> 45:20.456
[indistinct chatter]

45:20.500 --> 45:22.328
[elevator bell chimes]

45:24.983 --> 45:27.550
Uh, excuse me. Excuse me.

45:27.594 --> 45:29.248
Gentlemen,
what's this regarding?

45:29.291 --> 45:30.640
Mr. Lane and Ms. Reddick,
please.

45:30.684 --> 45:32.164
Uh, you just can't
come in here bar--

45:32.207 --> 45:34.079
This is a place of business.
You have to--

45:34.122 --> 45:37.212
-Excuse me! Excuse me.
-Stop!

45:37.256 --> 45:40.650
Don't you dare run.

45:40.694 --> 45:42.174
Agent Morris,
can we help you?

45:42.217 --> 45:44.176
-STR Laurie.
-This way.

45:44.219 --> 45:46.265
♪

46:04.849 --> 46:06.981
MORRIS:
Ladies and gentlemen,

46:07.025 --> 46:08.635
please stay exactly
where you are.

46:08.678 --> 46:10.724
We are executing
a federal search warrant.

46:10.768 --> 46:13.074
Officers will be
moving among you,

46:13.118 --> 46:15.990
confiscating your work product
and your computers.

46:16.034 --> 46:18.166
Do not touch that!
Get your hands away from it...

46:18.210 --> 46:19.820
Low-tech enough for you?

46:19.864 --> 46:22.431
Sometimes that's all you need.

46:22.475 --> 46:23.911
[clamoring continues]

46:24.912 --> 46:26.740
I, um...

46:26.784 --> 46:29.351
I broke your dorje.
I'm sorry.

46:29.395 --> 46:31.005
Oh, it's okay.

46:32.006 --> 46:34.400
It's in two pieces.

46:34.443 --> 46:36.924
I-I just don't know
how it happened.

46:37.925 --> 46:39.318
Don't worry about it.

46:39.361 --> 46:42.582
I got you this.

46:42.625 --> 46:44.976
It-It's different, I know.

46:47.761 --> 46:49.328
It's beautiful.

46:49.371 --> 46:52.810
I looked up the word dorje
in Sanskrit.

46:52.853 --> 46:55.160
It means unbreakable.

46:55.203 --> 46:58.424
So if I can keep
my hands off of it,

46:58.467 --> 47:00.687
I hope this one will be.
[stifled laugh]

47:00.730 --> 47:02.732
Is this gold?

47:02.776 --> 47:04.430
I don't know.

47:04.473 --> 47:07.912
Uh... yes.

47:10.001 --> 47:11.741
[sighs]

47:12.917 --> 47:15.049
Diane, I don't think I can
be your doctor anymore.

47:18.226 --> 47:19.532
Why?

47:19.575 --> 47:20.968
I suggest you see
Alyssa Schuman.

47:21.012 --> 47:23.144
No.

47:23.188 --> 47:26.452
I kissed you.
I'm sorry.

47:26.495 --> 47:28.106
It was a mistake,
inappropriate.

47:28.149 --> 47:29.847
I crossed the line.

47:29.890 --> 47:31.718
-Wecrossed the line.
-No, I did it.

47:31.761 --> 47:33.589
You were being professional.
It was me.

47:33.633 --> 47:37.158
No, it was me, too.
I crossed it, too.

47:38.812 --> 47:39.900
You crossed it, too?

47:39.944 --> 47:43.121
Diane, we can't.

47:44.992 --> 47:46.994
But if I'm not your patient?

47:48.691 --> 47:51.738
I will tell Dr. Schuman
to expect your call.

47:51.781 --> 47:54.262
Thank you for this.

48:04.664 --> 48:06.057
Please call Dr. Schuman.

48:14.195 --> 48:16.197
We crossed the line.

48:16.241 --> 48:18.286
[elevator bell chimes]

48:21.420 --> 48:24.814
♪

